Recommends: gstreamer1.0-icamerasrc
Description: On-demand Intel IPU7 camera activation for Lunar Lake systems
 Manages the Intel IPU7 camera HAL on ThinkPad X1 2-in-1 Gen 10 and similar
 Lunar Lake systems. The HAL is started only when an application opens the
 camera and fully shut down the moment the application stops, so the LED
 accurately reflects actual usage.
 .
 A single GStreamer process holds a dual-source pipeline: videotestsrc feeds
 black frames while idle; icamerasrc is started on demand when an application
 opens the camera and driven back to NULL (HAL released, LED off) when it stops.
 .
 The virtual camera device /dev/video32 ("IPU7 Camera") is visible to Zoom,
 Telegram, WeChat, Element, and other V4L2-based applications. A PipeWire
 node is also published for Flatpak and portal-based applications (Brave, Signal).
 .
 Requires icamerasrc and the Intel IPU7 Camera HAL to be installed separately.
